# Claw server execution

**This project’s lab host** is `clawbot` / `~/blackbox`. See **`remote-ssh-only-server-work.mdc`**: server-side work happens **only** in **Cursor Remote SSH** to that repo — **not** via batch `ssh` from a local Cursor workspace.

When the workspace **is** Remote SSH to `~/blackbox` on clawbot, you may run commands and edit files there as usual.

When the workspace is **local**, do **not** use SSH to clawbot to perform server work; direct the user to open Remote SSH first, or limit work to the local tree / Git operations appropriate to their workflow.

Repo path on server: **`~/blackbox`** unless stated otherwise.
